pageContext.claim: “In Iowa caucuses last winter, you know what happened there. You all reported on it, I think, very well. Right? Do you remember that one? It was not good, right? But in Iowa, they still don't really know who the winner was. I think they called somebody eventually, but it was many, many weeks later. But they really have no idea.”
pageContext.analysis: The Democrats have a vote count and have delegated Iowa’s delegates. However, the Associated Press declined to verify a winner.
